Townsend Acquires Bay Area's Legal Strategies Group



        By Marius Meland



					Law360, New York (February 12, 2004, 12:00 AM EST) -- San Francisco intellectual property boutique Townsend and Townsend and Crew LLP has acquired the Legal Strategies Group, a Bay Area law firm focused on commercial and IP litigation and dispute resolution, the firm said Wednesday.The acquisition will add 12 attorney's to the 150-attorney law firm, which specializes in intellectual property and complex litigation.The merger is effective March 1. Financial terms of the deal were not disclosed."This is a tremendous way to build upon our recent recognition as one of the top litigation departments...
				
